At least 300 officers were deployed at major taxi ranks in the city on Friday. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng traffic police say they ve impounded over 88 minibus taxis at the Noordt taxi rank in Johannesburg.At least 300 officers were deployed at major taxi ranks in the city on Friday in an operation to clampdown on unroadworthy vehicles.The blitz is expected to continue across the province over the next three weeks, as more minibus vehicles intend to travel long distances.The police's Busaphi Nxumalo says: The reason for impoundment is that some taxis don t have [licence] disks and others have safety defects. We will continue to monitor all taxi ranks. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)